        "creation_date": 1299259759,
        "answer_count": 11,
        "title": "Convert 1 to 01",
        "body": "<p>I have an int between 1 - 99. How do I get it to always be a double digit, ie: 01, 04, 21?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 5197144,
        "tags": ["java"],
        "score": 24,
        "accepted_answer_id": 5197291,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 67082
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4e645e1f9fd76b902f330ca8db5479f6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 41545,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 120808,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/120808/adam-batkin",
                "reputation": 53314,
                "display_name": "Adam Batkin",
                "accept_rate": 90
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 46,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299259994,
            "creation_date": 1299259994,
            "body": "<p>Presumably you mean to store the number in a String.<\/p>\n\n<p>Since JDK1.5 there has been the <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#format%28java.lang.String,%20java.lang.Object...%29\">String.format()<\/a> method, which will let you do exactly what you want:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String s = String.format(\"%02d\", someNumber);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>One of the nice things about String.format() is that you can use it to build up more complex strings without resorting to lots of concatenation, resulting in much cleaner code.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String logMessage = String.format(\"Error processing record %d of %d: %s\", recordNumber, maxRecords, error);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197199,
            "question_id": 5197144
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/53ee9941b3fefef67175daf212e62d41?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 23121,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 57695,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/57695/peter-lawrey",
                "reputation": 535107,
                "display_name": "Peter Lawrey",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 37,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1328041673,
            "creation_date": 1299260448,
            "body": "<p>Yet another way<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String text = (num &lt; 10 ? \"0\" : \"\") + num;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>EDIT: The code is short enough that the JIT can compile it to nothing. ;)<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>long start = System.nanoTime();\nfor(int i=0;i&lt;100000;i++) {\n    for(int num=1;num&lt;100;num++) {\n        String text = (num &lt; 10 ? \"0\" : \"\") + num;\n    }\n}\nlong time = System.nanoTime() - start;\nSystem.out.println(time/99/100000);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>prints<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>0\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197291,
            "question_id": 5197144,
            "last_edit_date": 1328041673
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/eb3e62e52e2a7b6b1c18b4932be13d19?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1700525,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1560744,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1560744/talisman",
                "reputation": 388,
                "display_name": "Talisman",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 23,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1344018968,
            "creation_date": 1344018968,
            "body": "<p>Using<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String.format(\"%02d\", num)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Is probably the best option.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 11801396,
            "question_id": 5197144
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/9pI1C.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 129700,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 328445,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/328445/matthew",
                "reputation": 44939,
                "display_name": "Matthew",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 15,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299273850,
            "creation_date": 1299260085,
            "body": "<p>You can do this with <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.4.2/docs/api/java/text/NumberFormat.html#NumberFormat()\" rel=\"noreferrer\">NumberFormat<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>NumberFormat format = new NumberFormat();\nformat.setMinimumIntegerDigits(2);\nSystem.out.println(format.format(1));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong>Note<\/strong> - <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/String.html#format(java.lang.String,%20java.lang.Object...)\" rel=\"noreferrer\">String.format()<\/a> is a Java 5 method.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you're using Java 5 or above you can do:<\/p>\n\n<p><code>String.format(\"%02d\", 1);<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>as mentioned in other answers.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197230,
            "question_id": 5197144,
            "last_edit_date": 1299273850
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1774afee7c4e54ec811b02aa5ee2c245?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 159523,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 378968,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/378968/dead-programmer",
                "reputation": 12615,
                "display_name": "Dead Programmer",
                "accept_rate": 87
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299260502,
            "creation_date": 1299260047,
            "body": "<p>Try this<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String.format(\"%02d\", num)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197215,
            "question_id": 5197144,
            "last_edit_date": 1299260502
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/mhoMH.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1762,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2405,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2405/william-brendel",
                "reputation": 32267,
                "display_name": "William Brendel",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299259975,
            "creation_date": 1299259975,
            "body": "<p>One possible solution:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String.valueOf(number + 100).substring(1);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197194,
            "question_id": 5197144
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "user_type": "does_not_exist",
                "display_name": "user634626"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299260664,
            "creation_date": 1299260664,
            "body": "<p>You can do this by<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String.format(\"%02d\", 1)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197324,
            "question_id": 5197144
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d8f540ed5300b2efbc389da170f9bf14?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 45046,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 132528,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/132528/jascav",
                "reputation": 34642,
                "display_name": "JasCav",
                "accept_rate": 99
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299259936,
            "creation_date": 1299259936,
            "body": "<p>You can't do it just using an int. You'll have to convert between Strings (for display) and back to ints (for calculations). You can use the <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Formatter.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Java Formatter<\/a> to format your Strings based on the input.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197187,
            "question_id": 5197144
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/38c6d672e1975b8ead85528142b85a65?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2026540,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1811356,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1811356/hardian",
                "reputation": 2022,
                "display_name": "Hardian"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1555342835,
            "creation_date": 1555342835,
            "body": "<p>I think, I should add the link to the official Java documentation on formatting numeric outputs.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/data/numberformat.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/data/numberformat.html<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Sample Snipplet: Prints 00 up to 100<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class Main {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n      for(int i=0;i&lt;=100;i++){\n        System.out.println(String.format(\"%02d\", i)); \n      }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Output:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>00\n01\n...\n10\n...\n100\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 55692760,
            "question_id": 5197144
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b8182c95cf5d0f427920118d6d2e4153?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 189393,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 428705,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/428705/vivek-goel",
                "reputation": 24440,
                "display_name": "Vivek Goel",
                "accept_rate": 76
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1299260014,
            "creation_date": 1299259934,
            "body": "<p>use number format \n<a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/NumberFormat.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/NumberFormat.html<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 5197186,
            "question_id": 5197144,
            "last_edit_date": 1299260014
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Kc9aW.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 6696504,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 5164373,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5164373/vishnu-kiran",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "Vishnu Kiran"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1572221424,
            "creation_date": 1572221424,
            "body": "<p>Or you could just use printf instead of String.format<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> for (int i = 0; i &lt;= 100; i++) {\n         System.out.printf(\"%02d%n\",i);\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 58584466,
